ZCZC OE43
OE43
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
TUESDAY TO FRIDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 192300 UTC
ON TUESDAY EVENING A LOW 979 LIES OVER THE ATLANTIC AT 59 N 31 W. THIS
LOW STRETCHES E AND DEEPENS TO BE 973 BAILEY BY MID-AFTERNOON WEDNESDAY WHILST
ANOTHER LOW 970 REMAINS IN THE ATLANTIC. THE BAILEYS LOW FILLS SLTLY AND
MOVS EWARDS OVER NORWAY AND THE ATLANTIC LOW DRIFTS EWARDS OVER HEBRIDES
969 BY THURSDAY AFTERNOON. FRIDAY SEES THE LOW FILL AND MOV S-W DOWN TO ROCKALL
SETTLING AT 988 BY FRIDAY EVENING. STRG WINDS N OF 59N AND S OF 53N WITH
ISOL GALES IN FAEROES AND SE ICELAND. THESE STRG WINDS BECOME REGIONWIDE
ACROSS PORTPATRICK BY MIDDAY ON WEDNESDAY WITH GALES ACCROSS BAILEY FAEROES
AND SE ICELAND. WINDS DECLINE IN MALIN AND ROCKALL BY EARLY THURDSAY MORNING
AND LUNDY AND IRISH SEA BY THURSDAY AFTERNOON AS THE LOW PRESSURE DRISTS
S-WWARDS. FRIDAY SEES STRG WINDS CONTINUE S AND N OF THE LOW WHICH IS NOW
OVER ROCKALL
